<!-- ABOUT -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>About Road Accidents</h2>
  <p>
    Road accidents involve collisions of vehicles, pedestrians, or cyclists due to human error,
    road conditions, weather, or mechanical failure.  
  </p>
  <p>
    India has one of the highest rates of road accidents in the world, making road safety skills extremely important.
  </p>
</article>

<!-- CAUSES -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Major Causes of Road Accidents</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Overspeeding</li>
    <li>Drunk driving</li>
    <li>Distracted driving (phones, eating, talking)</li>
    <li>Bad road conditions or potholes</li>
    <li>Skipping red lights</li>
    <li>Driving without seatbelt or helmet</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- WARNING SIGNS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Warning Signs Before an Accident</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Vehicle skidding or losing balance</li>
    <li>Sudden brakes by vehicles ahead</li>
    <li>Overloaded vehicles</li>
    <li>Sudden lane changes</li>
    <li>Fog reducing visibility</li>
    <li>High beams blinding drivers at night</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- SAFE DRIVING -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Safe Driving Practices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Always follow speed limits.</li>
    <li>Wear helmet/seatbelt at all times.</li>
    <li>Avoid using mobile phones while driving.</li>
    <li>Maintain safe distance between vehicles.</li>
    <li>Use indicators before turning or changing lanes.</li>
    <li>Drive slower during rain, fog, and night.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- PEDESTRIAN SAFETY -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Pedestrian Safety</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use footpaths and zebra crossings.</li>
    <li>Do not use headphones while crossing roads.</li>
    <li>Look both sides before crossing.</li>
    <li>Wear bright clothes at night for visibility.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- DO‚ÄôS & DON'Ts -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Do‚Äôs & Don‚Äôts</h2>

  <h3>‚úî Do‚Äôs</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Follow traffic signals strictly.</li>
    <li>Keep vehicle maintained.</li>
    <li>Slow down near schools & crowded areas.</li>
    <li>Use pedestrian crossings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>‚ùå Don‚Äôts</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Do NOT drink and drive.</li>
    <li>Do NOT overspeed.</li>
    <li>Do NOT drive when sleepy.</li>
    <li>Do NOT block ambulances.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- HELPING OTHERS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>How to Help During a Road Accident</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Call emergency number 112 immediately.</li>
    <li>Do not crowd the accident site.</li>
    <li>Help move injured people only if the location is unsafe.</li>
    <li>Stop bleeding using clean cloth.</li>
    <li>Give first aid until medical help arrives.</li>
    <li>Record license plate of offender if it's a hit-and-run.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

